MENG DIGITAL TWIN - CLONE AND RUN ON ANY PC
============================================

Purpose
-------
Use this checklist every time you open the project on a different PC so setup, execution, and Git syncing are consistent.

Prerequisites (install once per PC)
-----------------------------------
1. Git for Windows
2. Python 3.11+ (recommended)
3. VS Code (recommended)
4. Internet access for pip installs

Project Clone
-------------
1. Open PowerShell.
2. Go to where you want the project folder:
   cd "C:\Users\<YourUser>\Desktop"
3. Clone:
   git clone https://github.com/SiphesihleMabaso381/MENG_DIGITAL_TWIN_SIMULATION_IEEE.git
4. Enter project folder:
   cd MENG_DIGITAL_TWIN_SIMULATION_IEEE

Create Environment and Install Dependencies
------------------------------------------
Option A (recommended if setup.ps1 is available)
1. Run:
   powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\setup.ps1

Option B (manual)
1. Create venv:
   python -m venv .venv
2. Activate venv:
   .\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
3. Upgrade pip:
   python -m pip install --upgrade pip
4. Install requirements:
   pip install -r requirements.txt

IEEE Feeder Data Requirement
----------------------------
The full IEEE13 run needs feeder files in the expected path under ieee_feeders.
If missing, download and extract IEEE test feeders so this path exists:
- ieee_feeders/.../IEEE13Nodeckt.dss

Quick Health Checks
-------------------
1. Run demo:
   .\.venv\Scripts\python.exe main.py
2. Run full IEEE13:
   .\.venv\Scripts\python.exe main.py --full-ieee13
3. Generate dashboard:
   .\.venv\Scripts\python.exe src\dashboard.py --results-dir results/main_ieee --save results/main_ieee/dashboard.png --no-show

Where Outputs Go
----------------
1. main.py outputs:
   results/main_ieee/
2. example_simulation.py outputs:
   results/load_profiles.csv (when run directly)

Git Workflow (ALWAYS for local + remote sync)
----------------------------------------------
Do these steps every time you make edits and want them saved both locally and on GitHub.

1. Confirm branch and changed files:
   git status -sb

2. Pull latest remote changes before committing:
   git pull origin main

3. Stage files:
   git add -A

4. Commit locally (this is local save):
   git commit -m "Describe what changed"

5. Push to GitHub remote (this is remote save):
   git push origin main

6. Verify synced:
   git status -sb
   Expected: no pending changes and main aligned with origin/main.

If git is not found on PATH
---------------------------
Use explicit Git path:
"C:\Program Files\Git\cmd\git.exe"

Example:
& "C:\Program Files\Git\cmd\git.exe" status -sb

Daily Safe Routine
------------------
1. Open project folder.
2. Activate venv.
3. Pull latest: git pull origin main
4. Make edits.
5. Run project checks.
6. Commit + push.
7. Confirm sync with git status -sb.

Conflict Handling
-----------------
If push is rejected:
1. git pull origin main
2. Resolve conflicts in files.
3. git add -A
4. git commit -m "Resolve merge conflicts"
5. git push origin main

Reproducibility Note
--------------------
Simulation uses fixed seed in config for reproducible behavior.
You may still see tiny floating-point differences across hardware/OS, but trends and outcomes should match.
